                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.114M69/122.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1912</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of May 8. The Consul General at Smyrna telegraphed me May 11 that
                    the Governor General of Smyrna had informed <pb facs="1420" n="1316"
                        xml:id="pg_1316"/> him that the captain of the <hi rend="italic">Texas</hi>
                    was charged with having caused the sinking of the ship, resulting in the death
                    of many persons, through disobeying regulations concerning navigation during
                    war. The Consul General has requested delivery of the captain for his detention
                    in accordance with your instructions to me. I have also made representations to
                    the Foreign Office in the same sense<note n="1" xml:id="d1666fn1">See inclosure
                        3 with his despatch 234 of June 28.</note> and asked it to supply me with
                    certain data necessary to elucidation monetary [sic] facts. I have reserved all
                    questions of importance, claims and jurisdiction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
